			May 24, 2013 at 8:07 am</a>		</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

		<div class="comment-body"><p>Hi Thomas,</p>
<p>You add sound effects to this game the same way you would do any other flash game <img src="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" />  Look into the flsah.media.Sound class &#8211; but you&#8217;ll need to do some research on how to use it.</p>
<p>The enemies and map are edited and placed using the editor called Mappy. Please see the description in my original article:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/2011/12/11/how-to-make-a-2d-platform-game-part-1/" rel="nofollow">http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/2011/12/11/how-to-make-a-2d-platform-game-part-1/</a></p>
<p>Cheers, Paul.</p>
</div>

